d": ["NCBIGene:250"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ALP", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.993247926235199, "span": {"begin": 1323, "end": 1326}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:632"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "osteocalcin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9850825071334839, "span": {"begin": 1332, "end": 1343}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:632"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "OCN", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9963253140449524, "span": {"begin": 1345, "end": 1348}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:8600"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "receptor activator of nuclear factor kappa B ligand", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9967262148857117, "span": {"begin": 1428, "end": 1479}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:8600"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "RANK-L", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9947287440299988, "span": {"begin": 1481, "end": 1487}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "osteoclastogenesis", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.767587423324585, "span": {"begin": 1521, "end": 1539}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:8600"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "RANK-L", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9940410256385803, "span": {"begin": 1555, "end": 1561}}, {"id": ["CL:0000092"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "osteoclast", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8695786595344543, "span": {"begin": 1587, "end": 1597}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:35396"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "tartrate", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9984983205795288, "span": {"begin": 1662, "end": 1670}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:93650"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "tartrate-resistant acid phosphatase", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9961721301078796, "span": {"begin": 1662, "end": 1697}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:100187907"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TRAP", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9940018057823181, "span": {"begin": 1699, "end": 1703}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1513"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Cathepsin K", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9920520782470703, "span": {"begin": 1706, "end": 1717}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CTSK", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.5951486229896545, "span": {"begin": 1719, "end": 1723}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:17883"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "HCl", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9995613694190979, "span": {"begin": 1730, "end": 1733}}], "text": "The tight regulation of differentiation pathways leading to bone-forming osteoblasts (osteoblastogenesis) and bone-resorbing osteoclasts (osteoclastogenesis) is essential for the maintenance of osteogenic balance, i.e., the deposition and resorption of bone matrix. As such, perturbations by the overproduction of reactive oxygen species (ROS) during oxidative stress can have devastating effects on the delicate balance of bone cell (i.e., osteocyte, osteoclast, and osteoblast) differentiation and function.&nbsp;  Oxidative stress disrupts the homeostatic balance of osteoblastic bone deposition and osteoclastic bone resorption by altering the osteoblastogenic/osteoclastogenic differentiation pathways through the overproduction of ROS (Agidigbi and Kim, 2019; Tian et al., 2017). Briefly, ROS produced in pre-osteoblasts and pre-osteoclasts will affect the activities of different signaling molecules in the respective cell types. In osteoblasts, ROS naturally upregulate expression of the transcription factor forkhead box O (FoxO) which enhances cell antioxidant status. FoxO requires &szlig;-catenin binding, which sequesters &szlig;-catenin from the main osteoblast differentiation pathway, the Wnt/&szlig;-catenin pathway, ultimately downregulating osteoblastogenesis and the expression of alkaline phosphatase (ALP) and osteocalcin (OCN) (Manolagas and Almeida, 2007; Tian et al., 2017). Further, ROS upregulate the receptor activator of nuclear factor kappa B ligand (RANK-L), which is the main regulator of osteoclastogenesis. By increasing RANK-L production, ROS inhibits osteoclast apoptosis and promotes osteoclastogenesis and the expression of tartrate-resistant acid phosphatase (TRAP), Cathepsin K (CTSK), and HCl (Tian et al., 2017).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:58:45 +0000 2026"}